WhiteRose Properties, a real estate company, recently stepped up its game in the industry, when it launched Camelot Mews by WhiteRose Project in the highbrow Lekki axis of Lagos. The colourful open-house event held at Camelot Mews Orchid Road, Lekki, was attended by high-profile Nigerians and top industry professionals.   Winner gets car in Bigi’s ‘Watch & Win’ promo     Nigeria attracts fresh investments in pharmaceutical sector     FHA Mortgage Bank earns DataPro’s “BBB” rating   Camelot Mews by WhiteRose is a fine selection of 1 bedroom flat, 2 bedrooms flat and 4 bedrooms semi-detached. According to Ayobami Kareem, Founder and Group Managing Director of WhiteRose International Group, parent company of WhiteRose Properties, “The new luxury estate project strategically located in the ultra-rich neighbourhood is the big deal in Lagos property circle at the moment.” Better known for its strong track record of excellence, WhiteRose Properties has quickly climbed up the property ladder as one of Nigeria’s go-to property companies for luxury and affordability. The company’s impressive profile boasts a long list of exciting projects that includes Kirah Court 1 by WhiteRose, Oakview Estate, WhiteRose Mall, Kirah Court 2 by 4 bedroom fully detached duplexes with a room BQ and WhiteRose Court Conservation Centre al in Lagos.